President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. David Medine is nominated for Chairman of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. He has experience in privacy and data security, serving as a Senior Advisor to the White House National Economic Council and as Associate Director for Financial Practices at the Federal Trade Commission (FTC). Rachel L. Brand is nominated for Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. She currently serves as Chief Counsel for Regulatory Litigation at the U.S. Chamber of Commerce and has previously worked at the U.S. Department of Justice and as Associate Counsel to President George W. Bush. Judge Patricia M. Wald is nominated for Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. She served on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia for twenty years and has since held various roles, including as a Judge on the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia. She also has experience in the Department of Justice and has worked on issues related to mental health law and drug abuse research.